<item>
            <title>[LU-19971] FLR-EC: calculate correct file blocks for EC parity components in LSoM and getattr</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19971</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;stat() / getattr reports incorrect st_blocks for files with EC parity mirrors. Block accounting needs to correctly handle parity stripes &#8212; either they&apos;re not counted when they should be, or double-counted. Affects capacity planning (du/df) for EC files. Related to existing FLR mirror block counting bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14970&quot; title=&quot;sanity-flr test_50a: FAIL: Mirrored file consumes 1728 blocks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14970&quot;&gt;LU-14970&lt;/a&gt;. Migrated from EX-12852.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
